summary: PPSS #42: Let’s meet Debra, Peter’s grad school buddy with...hoo boy, literally the worst self-esteem I have ever seen in a...
caption:
PPSS #42:

Let’s meet Debra, Peter’s grad school buddy with…hoo boy, literally the worst self-esteem I have ever seen in a comic.

Peter, of course, will manage to make her feel even worse throughout this issue by abandoning her immediately after this panel.

Deb’s cute. I hope she gets some help and learns to appreciate and take care of herself. I’ll bring her back in my run on All-New, All-Different Frightful Four.

body:
Favorite bois

I was tagged by @acherik to do this, I actually remembered to do something I was tagged in! Miracle.

Write your top 10 favorite male characters (each can be from different fandom but not required) in no particular order:

1. Alexander Summers/Havok (Alexander dam he thick ~jacksfilms 2017)

2.Peter Parker/Spider-man (shy,nerdy obviously bi spider-boy)

3. Wade Wilson/Deadpool (merc with a mouth who spreads pansexual awareness)

4. Hank McCoy/Beast (big fluffy boy who needs more love)

5. Big Daddies- Bioshock (I really love their designs and are fucking badass. Bioshock 2 is my favorite of all 3 games because you get to play as a big daddy)

6. Wheatley- Portal (the moron who got shot into space)

7. Craig and Tweek- south park (I know this is cheating but I don’t really like one over the other, they are both beautiful boys in a relationship)

8. Pip Pirrup- South Park (you all forget him but this british boy will always be in my heart)

9. Beast- beauty and the beast (this is a weird one, I know. But Beauty and the best IS MY FAVORITE disney tale. I loved the beast and honestly didn’t even want to see him turn human again)

10. Pyramid head- Silent hill (another weird one, I LOVEEEE horror movies. And pyrimad head is one of my favorite representations of sexual frustration and aggression, the the player he is as real as you want him to be. I am a psychology student so it makes me appreciate him that much more)

I tagggg @comicus-peixes , @fflaminlo , @spidertea-art , and ah..you..yes you reading this.

body:
Septic Spider Man!

I’ve been working on this for quite a while, it’s one of the art pieces I’m most proud of.

I wanted to draw Sean as Spider-Man as I was inspired by his play through and he even said he loved seeing the fanart. I wanted to do something different and the first thing that popped into my head was this - A spider man, half man, half spider.

@therealjacksepticeye

summary: @therealjacksepticeye You’re a busy man and I don’t expect you to see this post amongst the probably thousands of @s you get,...
body:
@therealjacksepticeye You’re a busy man and I don’t expect you to see this post amongst the probably thousands of @s you get, but that’s okay, because it matters more that I say this within metaphorical earshot of you than that you see this at all.

Your series playing Marvel’s Spider-man this past two weeks has emotionally connected with me more than anything you’ve played in the past.  In part, because of the wonderful design and story of the game that was a fresh remix of the classic Spider-man lore; props to Insomniac for that.  But by and large, the most emotionally significant part of watching this play through was just seeing that you were equally thrilled (if not more-so!) to play the game as I was to watch you play it.  Your love for Spider-man is frankly spectacular.

Spider-man is and always has been a very important pop-culture icon to me; he represents the intellectual and try-hard everyman in society, and has remained consistently immune to the grimdarkness that continually tries to absorb the comic-book industry.  It’s only fitting that you, a man making his brand on a genuine Positive Mental Attitude, would love and care about Spider-man as much as I do.  I know you’ve heard fans mention their personal struggles to you before, but it’s no secret online that I deal with clinical depression, so I have to make the active choice to stay optimistic every day, to laugh at my own expense, and to try, try again.  Spider-man’s consistent positivity has always been a drawing factor for me, and same goes for yours.

So really, I just want to thank you for being you and having so much unfiltered fun these past 12 days (or, a day and a half a week and a half ago!).  Some changes I’m not so fond of are happening in my life, so your playthrough of the game came at just the right time.  Keep on being you Sean, you mean the world to a lot of us.

Also, having just laughed and cried through the final episode, isn’t it kind of funny that you got to be Green Spider-man at the end of it afterall?  That game was made for you man.  It’s amazing.

title: Spider-Man : La haute-voltige au rendez-vous
body:
Découvrez ma critique de #SpiderManPS4 : La haute-voltige au rendez-vous !

Fan du super héros mais pas spécialement hypé par le jeu vidéo, c’est en toute innocence que j’ai commencé les aventures new-yorkaises de Spider Man. Attendu par beaucoup, l’homme-araignée a affolé la toile avec ses très bonnes notes et critiques reçues. Mais que vaut vraiment cette nouvelle exclusivité Sony signée par le studio Insomniac Games responsable du sous-côté mais très bon Sunset…

Découvrez ma critique de #SpiderManPS4 : La haute-voltige au rendez-vous !

Fan du super héros mais pas spécialement hypé par le jeu vidéo, c’est en toute innocence que j’ai commencé les aventures new-yorkaises de Spider Man. Attendu par beaucoup, l’homme-araignée a affolé la toile avec ses très bonnes notes et critiques reçues. Mais que vaut vraiment cette nouvelle exclusivité Sony signée par le studio Insomniac Games responsable du sous-côté mais très bon Sunset…
